view.name: MTA Subway Major Incidents: Beginning 2020
view.description: Major Incidents are incidents that delay 50 or more trains, which cause the most disruption to customers. This dataset covers data from 2020 and on. For data between 2015 and 2019, use dataset https://data.ny.gov/Transportation/MTA-Subway-Major-Incidents-2015-2019/ereg-mcvp.

columns.name: month
columns.description: The month in which the Major Incidents are being calculated (yyyy-mm-dd).

columns.name: division
columns.description: The A Division (numbered subway lines) and B Division (lettered subway lines).

columns.name: line
columns.description: Each subway line (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, A, C, E, B, D, F, M, G, J, Z, L, N, Q, R, W, S 42nd, S Rock, S Fkln).

columns.name: category
columns.description: The six categories that fall under the definition of a Major Incident: Track, Signals, Persons on Trackbed/Police/Medical, Stations and Structure, Subway Car, and Other.

columns.name: count
columns.description: The number of major incidents that occurred per month and per subway line.

Dataset Summary.Granularity: Subway line, division, month, day type, delay category
